snippet.textDisplay: I honestly love that Brian actually can't/won't do some of these features.  It shows that 1) you don't have to be a pro at everything to be an amazing mountain biker (because he does some seriously hard shit), and 2) you don't have to take on every feature and conquer it if it's just not your thing.    Being 41 years old and only MTB'ing part time for a year, I can't bunny hop for shit, I can half ass manual for about 3 seconds, but riding trails is still super amazing.  And you don't need to do crazy jumps, and bunny hops, and whatever stunts to ride more serious trails like at Santos (I'm in Central Florida), or other places.  You can be 3 different types of an MTB'er, you can be a trail rider like Brian is, a 'stunt' rider where you can do every trick in the book, or you can be a combination of both which is what I see Seth as being.  Being any of those is OK, you don't have to be all of it to be a super skilled rider.

snippet.textDisplay: Ok, at first I was going to rip into Brian a bit.  However, since I’m a subscriber of his channel and I’ve seen what he’s ridden, I truly appreciate his humbleness here.  I legit love the fact that he’s one of the few youtubers that aren’t afraid to admit they can’t do something. It makes him so much more relatable, especially to an early 40yr old guy like me. If you can’t ride, you can’t make a living! Seth, you’re a beast and I love your content! Hope the Sampler is ok. Best group of guys waiting it out.  Content for days. I’d watch you guys just drink beers. Stay safe!
